# ============================================================================
# git-crypt: Transparent Encryption for Sensitive Files
# ============================================================================
# Files matching these patterns are encrypted at rest in the repository.
# They appear as normal plaintext when the repo is unlocked (after `git-crypt unlock`).
# When locked (or on GitHub), they're AES-256 encrypted binary blobs.
#
# To unlock:  git-crypt unlock /path/to/financial-manager-git-crypt.key
# To lock:    git-crypt lock
# To check:   git-crypt status
# ============================================================================

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tax preparation working notes (names, addresses, wages, account numbers)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
docs/tax-prep-notes-*.md filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Validation tests containing real accepted tax return data
# (W-2 wages, 1099 amounts, employer names, 1040 line items)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
